## Helm repositories

```sh
helm repo add grafana https://grafana.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo add minio https://charts.min.io/
helm repo update
```

The MinIO repository is only required when installing the generated MinIO storage option.

## Storage assumptions

Object storage is configured as `{{ .Storage.Type }}` with endpoint `{{ .Storage.Endpoint }}` and region `{{ .Storage.Region }}`.

The generated values reference placeholder Kubernetes secrets only. They do not contain real credentials. Create object storage secrets manually before installation and confirm the exact secret wiring expected by the Helm chart versions you use.

Expected object storage credential secret shape:

```yaml
accessKeyId:
  existingSecret: obsgen-object-storage
  existingSecretKey: access_key
secretAccessKey:
  existingSecret: obsgen-object-storage
  existingSecretKey: secret_key
```

See `storage/object-storage-notes.md` for bucket and secret assumptions.

## Install

Review all generated files before applying them to a cluster.

```sh
kubectl create namespace {{ .Namespace }}
{{ if eq .Storage.Type "minio" }}

helm upgrade --install minio minio/minio \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  -f storage/minio-values.yaml
{{ end }}

helm upgrade --install loki grafana/loki \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  -f values/loki-values.yaml

helm upgrade --install mimir grafana/mimir-distributed \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  -f values/mimir-values.yaml

helm upgrade --install tempo grafana/tempo-distributed \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  -f values/tempo-values.yaml

helm upgrade --install alloy grafana/alloy \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  -f values/alloy-values.yaml
```

You can also run:

```sh
./examples/install.sh
```

## Uninstall

```sh
./examples/uninstall.sh
```

The uninstall script removes Helm releases only. It does not delete PVCs, object storage buckets, or Kubernetes secrets by default.

## Production review checklist

- Replace placeholder secret references with secrets created and managed by your platform process.
- Confirm bucket names, lifecycle policies, encryption, network paths, and access policies.
- Review Loki, Mimir, and Tempo retention periods against compliance and cost requirements.
- Review replica counts, resource requests, persistence, topology spread, and disruption budgets.
- Verify chart versions and supported values keys before installing.
- Run a restore and deletion test for object storage before relying on the stack.

Generated configs should be reviewed before production use.
